original: Eilard, Axel Reinhold, stadsfogde, Borås, f. 9/5/94 i Vänersb. G. 26 m. Ulla Holm. Barn: Ulf f. 27, Björn 29, Eva 32, Terje 34, d. 41, Tönnes 38. — Stud :ex. i Gbg 14, jur. kand. v. Sthlm’s högsk. 21. Tings t jg. i Oppun-da o. Villåttinge här. doms. 21-22, tf. domhav. 23 o. 24, tf. rådman o. stadsfogde i Södertälje 24 o. 25, tf. rådman i Borås o. Jönköp. 24, tf. stadsfogde i Borås 25, stadsfogde där fr. 27. Skr.: Lagen om införsel (42), Införselexekutionen (47), div. tidskr:upps.
translated:
Eilard, Axel Reinhold was born on May 9th, 1894 in Vänersborg. He got married in 1926 to Ulla Holm and they had five children: Ulf (born in 1927), Björn (born in 1929), Eva (born in 1932), Terje (born in 1934, deceased in 1941) and Tönnes (born in 1938).

Eilard studied law and graduated from the University of Gothenburg in 1914 and from Stockholm University in 1921. He worked as a tingsnotarie (an assistant judge) in Oppunda and Villåttinge from 1921 to 1922, acted as a temporary judge in 1923 and 1924, was a temporary magistrate and stadfogde (a municipal court official) in Södertälje in 1924 and 1925, a temporary magistrate in Borås and Jönköping in 1924, a temporary stadfogde in Borås in 1925, and finally stadfogde in Borås from 1927.

Eilard authored two works; Lagen om införsel (The Import Law) in 1942, and Införselexekutionen (The Import Execution) in 1947. Additionally, he wrote articles for various periodicals.
